--- !u!114 &227070247
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 227070244}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Everybody likes <color=#00FFD5>Mint</color> arknights.\nAnd since fumo
    exists, everybody also likes <color=#00FFD5>Mint Arknights fumo</color>.\n\n<color=#00FFD5>Mint
    fumo</color>.\nMerely the thought about the existence of such greatness brings
    comfort, soothness, a peace within one's mind.\n\nSince ancient time, it was
    believed that: <color=#b1b1b1>\"Simply by owning <color=#00FFD5>Mint fumo</color>,
    simply by owning more of them, one can reach their peakest of strength, unleashing
    their inner potential to the fullest.\"</color>\n\nIt was, the peakest of line.\n\n<color=#00FFD5>Mint
    fumo</color> was believed.\n\n<color=#00FFD5>Mint fumo</color> was worshipped.\n\nLife
    was so beautiful.\n\n<color=#00FFD5>Mint fumo</color>. <color=#00FFD5>Mint fumo</color>.
    My <color=#00FFD5>Mint fumo</color>.\n\n...\n\n<color=#b1b1b1>\"But... has anyone
    even seen <color=#00FFD5>Mint fumo</color>?\"</color>\n\nAdmist the joys, a quetion
    raised. \n\nThe atmosphere changed into dead silence.\n\n<color=yellow>\"How
    does one own <color=#00FFD5>Mint fumo</color>?\"</color>\n\nWhat is this even
    about.\n\nSilly question. \n\nOf course we all know the answer, right?\n\n<color=#b1b1b1>\"How...
    does one own... <color=#00FFD5>Mint fumo</color>?\nHow does one own...\nHow do
    I...\n...\"</color>\n\n...\n\n...\n\nNobody, knew the answer.\n\n...\n\n...\n\nLife
    stopped being good, ever since then.\n\n...\n\nCenturies passed. And the answer
    to that question had never been found.\n\nHumanity worked day and night, studied,
    observed, hoped to find an answer, even a smallest clue would've been a great
    help.\n\nDespite all of that...\n\nNot even the tiniest bit of progress was made.\n\nHumanity
    was in utter despair. \n\nThey have lost all hope. \n\nThey was this near to
    accept the broken truth: <color=#00FFD5>Mint fumo</color>, perhaps, has never
    been real. \n\nWell, it was until they decided to ask me, who happened to have
    the answer, because I made up all this shit. Lmao.\n\n<color=yellow>So,</color>\nTo
    own <color=#00FFD5>Mint fumo</color>, you have to complete STAGES. Every stage
    can give you up to 2 <color=#00FFD5>Mint fumos</color>: One in Normal mode and
    one in <color=red>Challenge Mode</color>. That's all!\n\n...\n\nThe crowd cheered
    up.\n\nHaving heard the answer, humanity rejoiced.\n\nThey lit up the biggest
    fire to celebrate, which didn't make sense at all because we are in the modern
    society, no one celebrates like that wtf.\n\nWell, anyway.\nThough the previous
    searches for an answer didn't directly lead to an outcome, we had uncovered a
    lot of other truths about our surroundings, and learnt a lot of it.\n\nHence,
    it had been brought into the textbook, had a dedicated chapter under the name:\n<i>The
    <color=#00FFD5>Mint</color>'s researches.</i>"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 5302535af1044152a457ed104f1f4b91, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2100000, guid: b246c4190f4e46ec9352fe15a7b09ce0, type: 2}
